pageTitle: Album Sales Charts - Week Ending 2/14 - Rap Basement
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {4986=Posted by Jason on February 16, 2010 & filed under Sales Charts.}
textBeforeTable: On the R&B tip, Alicia Keys new "Element Of Freedom" album gained one spot this week to 12th while Mary J Blige is right behind her with just under 40-thousand-copies sold this week. Rihanna's "Rated R" album dropped twelve spots while Beyonce had her album drop 29 spots to 40th with just under 19 thousand copies sold.      Lil Wayne's new "Rebirth" album continued to do well this week only losing two spots (down to 4th) with another 83 thousand copies sold in it's second week while the Black Eyed Peas only decrease 7% in sales as their new "E.N.D." album moved close to sixty-six thousand more units. Weezy's Young Money album sells 19,400 plus Jay-Z's new "Blueprint 3" album lands at 44th. Posted by Jason on February 16, 2010 & filed under Sales Charts.
